The Food Standards Agency has launched an unprecedented probe into how a potentially cancer-causing dye contaminated at least 474 products.
Britain's Food Standards Agency on Friday issued an urgent warning advising people not to eat more than 350 food products inadvertently contaminated with an illegal dye.
The director of Food Standard Agency David Statham said in a statement that local authorities across the country have visited a number of premises to look at records and take samples.
